article.description: Evan Boudreaux scored 19 points and Dartmouth beat Canisius 80-69 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Dartmouth beats Canisius 80-69
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Evan Boudreaux scored 19 points and Dartmouth beat Canisius 80-69 Tuesday night. Boudreaux had six rebounds and four steals while hitting 10 of 12 free throws, including four straight after Canisius' Jermaine Crumpton was called for two technicals. The four free throws put the Big Green (5-9) up 15, 62-47, with 8:14 to play. The Golden Griffins (7-10) got back within five on a 3-pointer but Chris Atkinson but two free throws each from Malik Gill and Guilien Smith put Dartmouth up 12, 73-61, with 1:41 left. Dartmouth closed the first half on a 10-2 run to lead 33-31. Miles Wright added 14 points, Kevin Crescenzi 13 and Connor Boehm 11 for Dartmouth, which ended a three-game losing streak. Malcolm McMillan had 17 points, Kassius Robertson 12 and Kevin Bleeker 10 points and 11 rebounds -- including a career-high nine offensive boards -- for Canisius, which lost its fourth straight.
